snippet.textDisplay:
So for all those who didn't really understood the essence of this song ; How exactly it worked in Indian culture is when a girl is married she is suppose to leave her parents home and will go far away somewhere to her husband's,unlike nowadays in olden times women didn't get to go back to there parents often and also they were far from each other.So even if there parents are not well or alone there is nothing much to do.Boys get to live with their parents but girls did not.

This song is about a girl who says no matter what, i will be with you and will never leave you because i am your 'Laadki' meaning extremely dear and special daughter.She sends her love ,care and affection to her parents.

snippet.textDisplay:
Please listen. I will dedicate this to my daughter whenever I will have her. 
Magical. 
So much variety yet every element held its own as well as ornamented the song (except maybe the distortion guitar and shennai some how didnt seem to blend for me).
Shennai is SO WOW.
Shri Kirtidan is a diamond subtle, old soul, classic and so so brilliant. Rekhaji needs no words.
Sachin-Jigar have done an amazing arrangement here especially by bring together all these talented musicians. It's like creating a timeless piece of jewellery with the best of gems arranged to perfection.
